a_0.formal problem:
theorem
fixes a b :: complex
assumes h0 : "a = Complex (Re 9) (Im (-4))"
and h1 : "b = Complex (Re (-3)) (Im (-4))"
shows  "a - b = 12"
a_0.formal solution:
(* ### Problem
 Simplify $(9-4i)-(-3-4i)$. The final Answer is 12
 ### Proof
 $(9-4i)- (-3-4i) = 9-4i +3 +4i = (9+3) + (-4i+4i) = \boxed{12}$.
 *)

theorem
fixes a b :: complex
assumes h0 : "a = Complex (Re 9) (Im (-4))"
and h1 : "b = Complex (Re (-3)) (Im (-4))"
shows  "a - b = 12"
 proof- 
  show ?thesis sledgehammer
